PathAnalyzerTest create and update are
synchronous reread flows. OCI returns the body
immediately and the resource exposes only ACTIVE
and DELETED, so the reviewed runtime does not
publish provisioning or updating lifecycle
buckets.
Pre-create reuse always scopes by compartmentId
and only uses the SDK displayName filter when
spec.displayName is present, but adoption still
requires a unique exact match on the reviewed
identity surface.
The published status surface mirrors the
observed PathAnalyzerTest body, including the
polymorphic endpoint and protocol-parameter read
model.
Delete confirmation treats either a DELETED
lifecycle response or a NotFound reread as
terminal and otherwise keeps the finalizer until
OCI stops returning the resource.
end note
